You can copy this sheet and experiment on your own:

- Set your VIP level.

- Revalue items prices. I used suggestions from u/MickeyTheHunter with some modifications (I don't like to value things as 0)
https://new.reddit.com/r/IdleHeroes/comments/ckpqkf/tavern_quest_refresh_strategy_calculator/evppxfl/

Strategy X* <YY means that you should refresh any quest up to X* with value lower then YY. For example 6* <25 means that you should keep 3* quests with 25-30 Gems, but refresh 6* quests with Green Artifact Fragments. You can  filter first table to know what exactly to reroll.

Calculations is balanced by Item and rewards values. Best strategy doesn't gurantee event completion no matter what, but it optimizes the chances so it would be profitable. If you want to have better chances to complete quest - increase value of Glorious Relic.

I calculated two approaches - best strategy overal and hybrid approach. Overal best strategy you should use day to day. Hybrid approach suggests to change stategy each day depending on how much 7* quests you aldeady got. Hybrid strategy doesn't take into account how much other quest you got and assume you can complete it, So it allways suggests to reroll low value 6* quests (green arti). Don't use Hybrid strategy if Overal strategy dont suggest to reroll 6*!

I havent tested any strategies that involves: keeping track of income each day and change strategy to avoid losses, keepeng last one or two quests without refreshing to avoid long tail. I haven't also researched uses of quest scroll.
